The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                            BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, Jan. 2: The government will file cases against three Nandigram CPM leaders accused of beating up witnesses to the March 14 police firing for deposing before CBI sleuths.    
	CBI deputy inspector-general Alok Ranjan had told the government that the trio had to be arrested for a proper investigation into the firing. Home secretary Prasad Ranjan Ray said the government would file the cases soon.        
	Calcutta: Governor Gopalkrishna Gandhi opened South 24-Parganas fifth trade and commerce fair in Baruipur on Wednesday. About 25km from the city, Gandhi said the idea behind the fair was to create scope of employment in rural areas.         
	Burdwan: The Katwa subdivisional court sentenced 13 persons to life on Wednesday. They had killed brothers Sadhan Gopal Ghosh, 48, and Hriday, 42, and fled with their heads in the Ketugram area two years ago.                                                                                                                                                                       
